'''ArtRod''' is a nonprofit arts organization located in [[Tacoma, Washington]]. It was founded in 1958 and went through several incarnations including Allied Arts and Artists Exchange.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.artrod.org/history.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-03-04 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150213064818/http://artrod.org/history.html |archivedate=2015-02-13 |df= }}</ref><ref>Graves, J., 2005. Art in Tacoma's Present Links Past with Uncertain Future. The News Tribune. 2 Jan.</ref> The mission of ArtRod is to facilitate art exhibition in nontraditional public arenas and grew out of a response to bring [[contemporary art]] forms from a traditional [[museum]] setting and directly into the community's path.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.artrod.org/history.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-03-04 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150213064818/http://artrod.org/history.html |archivedate=2015-02-13 |df= }}</ref>
ArtRod has supported four major projects: ''[[Toby Room]]'' magazine, the [[Don't Bite the Pavement]] film series, and the exhibition spaces [[Tollbooth Gallery]] and [[Critical Line]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.artrod.org/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-01-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140516220118/http://artrod.org/ |archivedate=2014-05-16 |df= }}</ref> The organisation has been a collaboration between [[Michael Lent (visual artist)|Michael Lent]] and [[Jared Pappas-Kelley]].<ref>http://www.tacomaculture.org/arts/resource/TA_AMOCAT_2005.pdf</ref><ref>http://cityartsonline.com/issues/tacoma/2007/01/3-x-2</ref> In 2005 they were honoured with an arts genius award from the City of Tacoma for their work on ArtRod and the Tollbooth Gallery.<ref>http://www.tacomaculture.org/arts/resource/TA_AMOCAT_2005.pdf</ref>
