'''''Still Life with a Poem''''' is an [[oil painting]] by [[Spanish people|Spanish]] artist [[Juan Gris]], completed in 1915.<ref name="Sweet 2003">{{cite book | last=Sweet | first=D.L.H. | title=Savage Sight, Constructed Noise: Poetic Adaptations of Painterly Techniques in the French and American Avant-gardes | publisher=U.N.C. Department of Romance Languages | series=North Carolina studies in the Romance languages and literatures | year=2003 | isbn=978-0-8078-9281-7 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rCtZAAAAMAAJ | access-date=12 November 2018 | page=114}}</ref>
== Description == The painting is a [[still life]] in the style of [[cubism]] that depicts a table with a set of cards, a pipe and some bottles on it. A poem by [[Pierre Reverdy]] appears at the bottom.<ref>[http://www.nortonsimon.org/collections/browse_title.php?id=M.1968.08.1.P]. [[Norton Simon Museum]].</ref><ref name="Bray Gibbons McHale 2012 p. 325">{{cite book | last=Bray | first=J. | last2=Gibbons | first2=A. | last3=McHale | first3=B. | title=The Routledge Companion to Experimental Literature | publisher=Routledge | series=Routledge Literature Companions Series | year=2012 | isbn=978-0-415-57000-8 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Z3S2uf3Zj8AC&pg=PA325 | access-date=12 November 2018 | page=325}}</ref> {{clear}}
